When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

    If i want to work from a different computer or away from home I could certainly benefit from the 
    remote repository. Also if I wanted to shwre my work with others. 

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

    Maybe I want to keep some files for my personal use and not share them with others. 

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

    I can fork a repository from another person, then clone it to my local system. 

